ins for NPD Innovations and Business Cases Responsible for all financial compliance (including statutory audits, financial statements, overseeing VAT and Corporate Tax computations, etc.) Ensure that organisational changes and developments are financially sound and sustainable Drive the continuous development and enhancement of systems, processes and procedures to improve analysis, reporting and decision-support Deliver bespoke financial information and guidance for key strategic and operational decisions Represent the ASPAC Business at Group Level and to external stakeholders, as required The Preferred Candidate: Possess a Bachelor Degree as well as being a qualified Accountant.? A proven track record of Financial Leadership and delivery of financial performance at a regional level Extensive strategic financial management, analytics and commercial experience in FMCG/retail trade In-depth knowledge of accounting and financial principles across Asia Pacific Experience of working in multiple international markets in FMCG industry Strong motivational skills and ambition High energy, high creativity but ability to work through the basics too Experience of leading and influencing in an environment of rapidly changing workload, tight deadlines, in the context of high client expectations and tight time frames Superb commercial acumen and strong appreciation of the challenges of growing a business through retail Experience of initiating, leading and implementing programmes of work including organisational change High level of ability in terms of project planning, prioritisation and critical thinking will be essential Strong mathematical abilities and analytical skills; detail oriented and well organised Excellent computer skills and very strong command of Excel and other relevant applications Experience of SAP and Business Objects is highly desirable Ability to work under own initiative and drive process improvements Excellent written presentations ", 
